# NickelTypeFix

Fixes several text-rendering problems in Kobo's reader (firmware 4.x). Each fix is independent and
fails safe — it only engages where its seam exists, and never breaks the device. Nothing is
written to any device library on disk; a reboot without the mod is stock. Causes + mechanisms are
in ABOUT.md in the repo.

Fixes:
- Glyph "wobble": some fonts render letters a pixel too high/low; loaded unhinted to flatten it.
- Vertical (tategaki) CJK text coming out sideways under optimizeLegibility; corrected.
- Justified kepubs with uneven gaps at sentence boundaries under optimizeLegibility (the main
  one); fixed in Qt's justifier.
- Justification skewing around dashes/quotes/ellipses; secondary fix.
- Reader font falling back to the system font in a kepub chapter; the reading font is re-applied
  on each chapter so a chapter that drew before the font was ready gets corrected in place.
- Letter-spacing (tracking) that widens the letters but not the spaces, so tracked text (a styled
  title, say) runs its words together; the spaces are given the same tracking so words stay apart.
- Capital spacing (cpsp): a feature meant only for all-caps text, applied to ordinary text too, so
  capitals get an oddly wide gap after them; stripped from each font as it loads, for any font.

## Config (KOBOeReader/.adds/nickel-type-fix/config) — auto-created on first boot

- ntf_enabled:1            master switch; 0 = do nothing
- ntf_no_hinting:1         glyph "wobble" fix; 0 = stock rendering
- ntf_hinting_allowlist:   comma-separated families to leave hinted, e.g. Georgia, Kobo Nickel
- ntf_vertfix:1            vertical (tategaki) text fix
- ntf_justify_kospan:1     justified-kepub boundary fix (the main justify fix)
- ntf_justify_punct:1      punctuation justification fix
- ntf_kepub_fontfix:1      reader-font fallback fix; re-applies the reading font per kepub chapter
- ntf_letterspace_spaces:1 give spaces the same letter-spacing as the letters (tracked text)
- ntf_cpsp_fix:1           strip cpsp so capitals aren't spaced apart in body text (any font)
- ntf_log:0                verbose per-fix log to nickel-type-fix.log; off by default

A healthy boot logs nothing; problems are always logged regardless, and a mistake in the config
file (a misspelled setting, an invalid value) turns full verbose logging on for that boot so it
diagnoses itself. Set ntf_log:1 to also log each
fix engaging. Changes take effect on reboot. Delete the `uninstall` file and reboot to remove.
